From: Dynamic Devices <info@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
Subject: [PATCH] net: fec: imx8mq: enable DELAYED_CLKS for RGMII internal delay DT props

fec_imx8mq_info did not set FEC_QUIRK_DELAYED_CLKS_SUPPORT, so fec_enet_open()
never wrote FEC_ENET_TXC_DLY / FEC_ENET_RXC_DLY to ENET_ECR even when the device
tree set tx-internal-delay-ps / rx-internal-delay-ps (binding allows 0 or 2000 ps).

On i.MX8M Mini the ENET_ECR delay bits are functional (validated on DT510 via
/dev/mem). Align imx8mq-class FEC with imx8qm's delay capability so DT-controlled
RGMII internal delays reach the MAC.

Upstream-Status: Pending [hardware-validated on imx8mm; submit after NXP review]

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
@@ -159,8 +159,9 @@ static const struct fec_devinfo fec_imx8mq_info = {
 		  FEC_QUIRK_ERR007885 | FEC_QUIRK_BUG_CAPTURE |
 		  FEC_QUIRK_HAS_RACC | FEC_QUIRK_HAS_COALESCE |
 		  FEC_QUIRK_CLEAR_SETUP_MII | FEC_QUIRK_HAS_MULTI_QUEUES |
 		  FEC_QUIRK_HAS_EEE | FEC_QUIRK_WAKEUP_FROM_INT2 |
-		  FEC_QUIRK_HAS_MDIO_C45,
+		  FEC_QUIRK_HAS_MDIO_C45 |
+		  FEC_QUIRK_DELAYED_CLKS_SUPPORT,
 };
 
 static const struct fec_devinfo fec_imx8qm_info = {
